text:
I occasionally still use these free tools:
• <https://keywordtool.io/|Keyword Tool> (focusing on using autocomplete to generate keywords)
• <https://searchresponse.io/|Search Response> (keyword research focused on PAA questions and PASF queries)
And <https://www.link-assistant.com/seo-spyglass/|SEO Spyglass> looks like a good free option to research competitor backlinks, but I haven't used it myself.

For sure, a cheers to you :champagne: :clinking_glasses:  in growing to a point where this budget question feels moot!

Not exactly the same situation, but our agency turned 3 years old this month... and I remember when the ask for affording the lowest Ahrefs plan was just not a budgetary option. Now, we've upgraded it several times and pay for several other high-quality tools — it will happen, and it is the BEST feeling when it does!
